	<text>
		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001440_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="village">Shupanga</settlement></placeName> 31<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> May
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>1859</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">To The
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Commander of
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/><orgName><choice><sic>Her Majestys</sic><corr>Her Majesty's</corr></choice></orgName> Ship -</p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Sir</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I took the liberty 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>of applying to <persName><term type="occupation">Admiral</term>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Sir Frederick Grey</persName> about 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>the beginning of the present
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>year for some <term type="foodstuff">salt</term> provisions 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>for our crew and <space extent="3" unit="chars"/>the 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/><orgName>Expedition</orgName>, and hoped that 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>it would be in the <term type="occupation">Admiral's</term>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>power to send a vessel 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>with them to the <placeName><geogName type="mouth">Mouth of 
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>the <placeName><geogName type="river">Kongone</geogName></placeName></geogName></placeName> on the 24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>May, but no ship appearing 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001440_0002"/><!--pb/@n='02'-->
<lb/>on that day either the <placeName><geogName type="river">Kongone</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>or <placeName><geogName type="river">Luabo</geogName></placeName> <placeName><geogName type="mouth">mouths of the <placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName></geogName></placeName>
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I conclude that <bibl>my letter</bibl> may 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>may have been detained in the way 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>or that the service required 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>all the ships elsewhere - We 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>buried a bottle on the island <!-- geog:  --> 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>in the entrance to <placeName><geogName type="harbor"><placeName><geogName type="river">Kongone</geogName></placeName> 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>harbour</geogName></placeName> ten yards Magnetic 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>North of a + cut on one 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>of the supports of what was 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>the flag staff containing an 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>appointment for the 30<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>of July next in the same 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>harbour. <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>It contained also <!-- geog: Kongone harbor -->
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>some account of our movements 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>and of the discovery of a large 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>inland Lake to which we propose 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>to return after visiting <space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="village">Tette</settlement></placeName>. </p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001440_0003"/><!--pb/@n='03'-->
<lb/><p>The <bibl>despatches</bibl> accompanying 
<lb/>this <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>are of importance as 
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>the <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>first information 
<lb/>respecting the New Lake to 
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>our own <orgName>Government</orgName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>It is scarcely necessary to 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>mention this as any 
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><bibl>despatches</bibl> committed to your 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>charge will without doubt 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>be carefully preserved. 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>What is said in the <bibl>buried 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>letter</bibl> is for your own 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>private information and 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>that of the <term type="occupation">Admiral</term>. We say 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>little to the <term type="people">Portuguese</term> beyond 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>the fact of having discovered 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>a large Lake called <placeName><geogName type="lake">Shirwa</geogName></placeName>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>As yet they have made no 
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>pretensions to a previous knowledge 
<lb/><space extent="7" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>of it

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001440_0004"/><!--pb/@n='04'-->
<lb/>We have had some <term type="ailment">fever</term> 
<lb/>but of a mild form 
<lb/><persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Kirk</persName> and I have escaped</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/>I have the honour to be
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="words"/>Sir
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Your most obedient
<lb/><space extent="5" unit="words"/>servant</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/><term type="occupation">Consul</term>,
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/>commanding <orgName><placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> Expedition</orgName></p>
			
</div>
